# IMPORTANT: Update SMTP Password

The Hostinger email migration is complete, but you need to update the SMTP password in .env.local

## Steps to Get Your SMTP Password:

1. Log in to your Hostinger account
2. Go to Email section
3. Click on your email account: info@consularly.com
4. Find "Email Configuration" or "SMTP Settings"
5. Copy your email password

## Update .env.local:

Replace this line:
SMTP_PASSWORD=YOUR_HOSTINGER_PASSWORD_HERE

With your actual password:
SMTP_PASSWORD=your_actual_password

## Then Test:

1. Start your dev server: npm run dev
2. Navigate to admin dashboard
3. Use the EmailAliasManager component to send a test email
4. Or use the API: POST /api/admin/test-email

